Phase 7 #2 — Install vitest + write smoke test (auth.register coverage as first real test)

Why this is next:
- Closes the Rule 25 TDD deferral taken in Phase 7 #1 (auth.register)
- Compounding return: every subsequent Phase 7 ticket gets proper test-first ordering
- Self-contained, no credential blockers (unlike forgot-password → SMTP ⏳, join-by-token → LiveKit ⏳)
- Fresh-context friendly: Sonnet dispatch stays well under 30K budget

Scope (estimated Tier 2, ~5-7 files):
- Add vitest + @vitest/coverage-v8 to apps/web devDependencies
- apps/web/vitest.config.ts — Node test env (server-side tRPC) + path aliases matching tsconfig
- Wire root turbo.json test pipeline if needed
- apps/web/package.json — "test" script: vitest run; "test:watch": vitest
- Recreate apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/auth.test.ts (Sonnet's earlier draft is in git history at commit ce709ff parent — but easier to rewrite given Prisma mock structure changed)
- Tests: happy path returns { ok, slug }; rate-limit blocks before turnstile; turnstile fail → UNAUTHORIZED; slug conflict → CONFLICT; Zod rejects weak password + uppercase slug

After this lands, Phase 7 #3 candidates (any order):
- forgot-password tRPC (#2 from punch-list) — pairs with #1, but needs SMTP ⏳ to test email delivery
- /app/meetings/new form (#5) — visible product win, no blockers
- JWT org slug encoding (#4) — middleware foundation, high-risk; save for a careful session
- join/[token] tRPC (#3) — needs LiveKit keys ⏳ to test guest token exchange
- Socket.IO auth middleware (#7) — depends on session shape clarity
- Root landing page (#6) — verify scope first (current /page.tsx is 11 lines)
